@node "srf" "SpeedRacerFX"

@{fg shine} SpeedRacerFX@{fg text}

           SpeedRacerFX is based a bit around an old C64/Amiga game called Trailblazer,
 this involved speeding along as a ball object jumping over/avoiding blocks and
 running over the turbo squares. The difference with SpeedRacer is there is no ball
 it is just a screen that moves along at a fast pace. Although the levels are made up
 of blocks and not carefully drawn graphics you are not really bothered because the
 game moves as such a good speed your more concentrating on dodging the next block. As 
 with Trailblazer you can collect turbo squares which ofcource speed you up for a certain
 amount of time. Another added bonus is there is a level editor to play around with
 just incase you get bored with the 25 odd levels supplyed. The only one problem I
 found was that the computer was just to good, but in two player mode this game is
 excelent and well worth a download.

