@node "sfw" "PREVIEW"

@{fg shine} ALMAGICA - Scions of a Forgotten World@{fg text}

           This game is only in it's early stages so therefore this is not a review but
 a preview. The full game is to be released near the end of '97 and it looks to be a
 great game. The game is based around Dune & Settlers where you have a bunch of men at
 your disposal. Each person has there own job ie. farmer or fighter. The idea is to
 defeat the other enemy villages to go onto the next level. This isn't as easy as it
 seems because you have to build Blacksmiths, Wells, Inns and other various buildings
 to keep you alive and to make more soldiers and farmers. Aswell as the fighting aspect
 of the game you also have to get your farmers to harvest the gold mines and forests to
 get wood and money to build up your village. The enemys aren't exactly hard to defeat but
 you normally need two of your soldiers to defeat one of theres. As you progress you
 will find more people at your disposal with people like Archers and Scouts becoming
 avalible. This game is only in its very early stages but if the full game is like
 this I for one will be buying it.

