           Popper as you may guess is a pop up menu and at last it is one that
 works properly. The idea around popper is insted of going to the top of the 
 screen to get to the menu you just press the RMB anywhere on the screen and
 a tidy menu will appear right under the pointer. The only problem I found with
 Popper is there are no prefs so you can't change the colour of the menu and on
 my WB the background colour of the menu was a horrible brown, don't let that put
 you off though as Popper saves that little bit extra time and it's easy to use.
 Once you have run Popper every menu on every screen is changed so it is not just
 limited to the Workbench screen. This is a great little program that improves the
 Workbench that bit more.

 @{b}Avalible from@{ub} : Aminet/BBSes
 @{b}Archived name@{ub} : Popper40.lha

 Overall 79% out of 100%

